External Data Integration
Benchmark Data Sources
1. Industry Benchmarks
Sources:

IBISWorld: Industry reports (paid subscription, ~$1000/year)
Statista: Statistical data (freemium model)
BizMiner: Financial benchmarks by industry/size (paid)
Pipeline:

Scheduled Download: Airflow DAG fetches monthly reports
Parsing: PDF/Excel â†’ structured JSON (via LLM extraction or tabula-py)
Validation: Check data ranges, flag outliers
Storage: external_benchmarks table
API: GET /v1/benchmarks?industry=X&metric=Y
2. Competitor Intelligence
Sources (legal compliance required):

Public Financials: SEC filings, annual reports
Web Scraping: Pricing pages (robots.txt compliant)
Aggregated Datasets: Crunchbase, PitchBook (paid)
Privacy: Aggregate data only (min 5 companies per peer group)

3. Economic Indicators
Sources:

FRED API: Federal Reserve Economic Data (free)
World Bank API: Global development indicators (free)
US Census Bureau: Business statistics (free)
Metrics: CPI, unemployment rate, GDP growth, consumer confidence

Pipeline: Daily Airflow DAG fetches latest data

4. Compliance Standards
Sources:

AICPA: Audit standards (free public resources)
NIST: Cybersecurity framework (free)
ISO: ISO 27001, SOC2 checklists (manual curation)
Storage: Structured questionnaires in PostgreSQL